{"info": {"author": "Raphael Meudec", "author_email": "raphael.meudec@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7"], "description": "# gpumonitor\n\n`gpumonitor` gives you **stats about GPU** usage during execution of your scripts and trainings,\nas [TensorFlow](https://www.github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow) or \n[Pytorch Lightning](https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning) callbacks.\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"./assets/callbacks.png\" width=\"800\" />\n</p>\n\n\n## Installation\n\nInstallation can be done directly from this repository:\n\n```\npip install https://github.com/sicara/gpumonitor/archive/master.zip\n```\n\n## Getting started\n\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"./assets/gpumonitor.gif\" width=\"1000\" />\n</p>\n\n### Option 1: In your scripts\n\n```python\nmonitor = gpumonitor.GPUStatMonitor(delay=1)\n\n# Your instructions here\n# [...]\n\nmonitor.stop()\nmonitor.display_average_stats_per_gpu()\n```\n\n### Option 2: Callbacks\n\nAdd the following callback to your training loop:\n\nFor [TensorFlow](https://www.github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow),\n\n```python\nfrom gpumonitor.callbacks.tf import TFGpuMonitorCallback\n\nmodel.fit(x, y, callbacks=[TFGpuMonitorCallback(delay=0.5)])\n```\n\nFor [PyTorch Lightning](https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning),\n\n```python\nfrom gpumonitor.callbacks.lightning import PyTorchGpuMonitorCallback\n\ntrainer = pl.Trainer(callbacks=[PyTorchGpuMonitorCallback(delay=0.5)])\ntrainer.fit(model)\n```\n\n\n## Sources\n\n- Built on top of [GPUStat](https://github.com/wookayin/gpustat)\n- Separate thread loop coming from [gputil](https://github.com/anderskm/gputil)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/sicara/gpumonitor", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "gpumonitor", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/gpumonitor/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/gpumonitor/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/sicara/gpumonitor"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/gpumonitor/0.1.0/", "requires_dist": ["gpustat (>=0.6.0)", "bumpversion (>=0.5.3) ; extra == 'publish'", "twine (>=1.13.0) ; extra == 'publish'"], "requires_python": ">=3.6", "summary": "GPU Monitoring Callbacks for TensorFlow and PyTorch Lightning", "version": "0.1.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>gpumonitor</h1>\n<p><code>gpumonitor</code> gives you <strong>stats about GPU</strong> usage during execution of your scripts and trainings,\nas <a href=\"https://www.github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow\" rel=\"nofollow\">TensorFlow</a> or\n<a href=\"https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning\" rel=\"nofollow\">Pytorch Lightning</a> callbacks.</p>\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/a1bb91733b5b48c7f1168039ba360f4f51ab5b13/2e2f6173736574732f63616c6c6261636b732e706e67\" width=\"800\">\n</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Installation can be done directly from this repository:</p>\n<pre><code>pip install https://github.com/sicara/gpumonitor/archive/master.zip\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Getting started</h2>\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/809691a5ff68d831a2bfbd9b305ce0d56aed2d67/2e2f6173736574732f6770756d6f6e69746f722e676966\" width=\"1000\">\n</p>\n<h3>Option 1: In your scripts</h3>\n<pre><span class=\"n\">monitor</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">gpumonitor</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">GPUStatMonitor</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">delay</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\"># Your instructions here</span>\n<span class=\"c1\"># [...]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">monitor</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">stop</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n<span class=\"n\">monitor</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">display_average_stats_per_gpu</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n<h3>Option 2: Callbacks</h3>\n<p>Add the following callback to your training loop:</p>\n<p>For <a href=\"https://www.github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow\" rel=\"nofollow\">TensorFlow</a>,</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">gpumonitor.callbacks.tf</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">TFGpuMonitorCallback</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">model</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">fit</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">y</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">callbacks</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">TFGpuMonitorCallback</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">delay</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mf\">0.5</span><span class=\"p\">)])</span>\n</pre>\n<p>For <a href=\"https://github.com/PyTorchLightning/pytorch-lightning\" rel=\"nofollow\">PyTorch Lightning</a>,</p>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">gpumonitor.callbacks.lightning</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">PyTorchGpuMonitorCallback</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">trainer</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">pl</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Trainer</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">callbacks</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">PyTorchGpuMonitorCallback</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">delay</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mf\">0.5</span><span class=\"p\">)])</span>\n<span class=\"n\">trainer</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">fit</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">model</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Sources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Built on top of <a href=\"https://github.com/wookayin/gpustat\" rel=\"nofollow\">GPUStat</a></li>\n<li>Separate thread loop coming from <a href=\"https://github.com/anderskm/gputil\" rel=\"nofollow\">gputil</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7145790, "releases": {"0.1.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "1dc9ba51120bd980597ed2a5423527d6", "sha256": "25d917cd5db6848613974bc40672f57d9e3c086b45e03ccf5a6be392fa77e37f"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "gpumonitor-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "1dc9ba51120bd980597ed2a5423527d6", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 4122, "upload_time": "2020-05-01T15:26:06", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-05-01T15:26:06.379433Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/7a/58/6186128b29ed6fccafa8d4ffd2a66cf8f3dc13a6d7527bf4d8c9d11c9d07/gpumonitor-0.1.0-py3-none-any.whl", "yanked": false}, {"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "2f935da0d3fb3a4414768599d72fa687", "sha256": "e1b68625bd3b1a331d0eeaf44158e3e5981b948468a262c2dc2123cc8a00fb93"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "gpumonitor-0.1.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "2f935da0d3fb3a4414768599d72fa687", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": ">=3.6", "size": 3103, "upload_time": "2020-05-01T15:26:08", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-05-01T15:26:08.853082Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/f1/84/3df57638f8c22dbdeabc7148c186afbc45dc8474c36bf21afabaa419ebe0/gpumonitor-0.1.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}]}, "urls": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "1dc9ba51120bd980597ed2a5423527d6", "sha256": "25d917cd5db6848613